// Inlined tech-stack logos used by /architecture. Generated by
// scripts/fetch-tech-icons.sh. DO NOT EDIT BY HAND — re-run the script and
// commit the result.
//
// Why inline: Safari's Strict tracking-prevention silently drops <img>
// requests to cdn.simpleicons.org (the Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy quirk
// walletIcons.ts already documents). Inlining the SVGs as data: URLs
// removes the cross-origin fetch entirely AND removes a deploy-day risk
// that the CDN could go down during a demo. Mermaid 10 accepts data: URLs
// in <img src="..."> nodes the same way it accepts regular URLs, so the
// topology diagram still renders identically.
//
// Each entry is a base64-encoded SVG. Simpleicons-sourced entries embed
// the requested fill color in the SVG itself; hand-drawn monograms
// (phantom, anchor, pyth) are written directly in the script because
// those brands are not on cdn.simpleicons.org. Regenerate by running:
//
//   bash scripts/fetch-tech-icons.sh
//
// then committing the diff.

/* eslint-disable max-len */

